In [6]:
%%time 

res = []

for cryst_desc_column in correlation_df.columns[:N]:
    for solv_desc_column in correlation_df.columns[N:]:
        
        cdf = correlation_df[[solv_desc_column, cryst_desc_column]].dropna()

        solvent = cdf[solv_desc_column]
        crystal = cdf[cryst_desc_column]

        r, p_val = pearsonr(crystal, solvent)
        res.append([cryst_desc_column, solv_desc_column, cdf.shape[0], r, p_val])

In [18]:
N = 15
fig, ax = plt.subplots(nrows=N//3, ncols=3, figsize=(18, 6*N//3))

for i, (_, (d1, d2)) in enumerate(corr_df.sort_values(by=['p_value_corr', 'p_value'], ascending=True).head(N)[['crystal desc', 'solvent desc']].iterrows()):
    axis = ax[i//3, i%3]

    c_df = correlation_df[[d1, d2]].dropna()

    axis.scatter(c_df[d1], c_df[d2], s=300, alpha=.5, color='navy', edgecolor='gold')

    axis.set_title(r'$\rho$: {:.3f}, $r$: {:.3f}'.format(spearmanr(c_df[d1], c_df[d2])[0],
                                                         pearsonr(c_df[d1], c_df[d2])[0]))
    axis.set_xlabel(r'$\Delta$' + d1.replace('_px', ''))
    axis.set_ylabel(r'$\Delta$' + d2)

fig.tight_layout()
